* Carnage stretched as she came out of the CR chamber after a long repair, she sighed and began to make her way towards the bridge to see if she could find Cyber Claw.
On her way she passed a few interesting doors and rooms but one room in particular caught her optics, it was a door with a lion and dragon on it. She walked up to it and placer a delicate hand on the ornate carvings, they were beautiful! Like nothing she had ever seen, they also seemed so alive!
Carnage looked over the carvings with extreme care and persuasion to make sure that her optics missed nothing, with such a beautiful door there was surely treasures behind it.
She smiled at the thought of such treasures, weapons that nobot had ever seen, tactical scrolls, jewel studded swords and axes, everything an assassin could possibly ask for!
Carnage wanted to see what was on the other side of that door so much but when she went to open it it was locked, she growled but then thought that no lock could stop her from entering. But one thing did, the face that this wasn't her base and she was a stranger here.
She sighed as she turned away from the door, besides...there was always tomorrow.*
